I know you guys might see me at the gas pump giving health and wellness tips- one tip you may have seen this week is the importance of blue light glasses! I am obsessed with my blue light glasses- and all they do for my health- Experts continue to reveal the harmful effects of artificial blue light emitted from our LED lights, computers, smartphones and tablets…. particularly over time. When you intake too much artificial blue light, the melanopsin receptors in your brain interpret the light as daytime. This prevents the release of melatonin in your brain, which interrupts your circadian rhythm. This can disrupt your sleep, play a role in the development of cardiovascular disease & type 2 diabetes, and cause problems with your memory. To start protecting yourself, follow the QR code at the pump to get your own pair!! @fueledbygstv

My trip to greece wasn’t all about island hopping and fun. I had a mission. I have dreamed about going to  Aegina. For those of you who don’t know about it- Aegina is a small island in the Gulf of Greece, located just 16 miles southwest of Athens. Saint Nektarios, the patron saint of the island, was a prominent figure in the Greek Orthodox Church in the early 20th century and is known for his healing miracles. Saint Nektarios is considered a patron saint for people who are suffering from diseases; such as cancer, heart trouble, joint pain, epilepsy, arthritis and more. Ever since my mom and I were diagnosed with brain tumors friends would tell us they were going there to pray for us. We attended St. Nectarios church in California but going to his church in Greece was always the dream. I wanted to say thank you for all the miracles and healings we have been blessed with. It was our first stop on the trip. They say the faithful can hear St. Nectarios in the tomb. As soon as I kneeled down I heard knocking. Faint knocking noises. I asked Joanna our friend guiding us if that was him and she said yes. But I couldn’t believe it. I stayed ear to the tomb for a long time. I prayed to St. Nectarios and said please make it undeniable. I don’t want to leave here unsure if I heard you. As I was praying for the people in my life with cancer I heard a massive bang and started screaming I hear him! It was definitely undeniable. I sobbed with joy. It was so emotional as I feel I have such a connection with him and this just made me feel even more grateful for our connection. I will never forget this incredibly inspiring moment. I also got to sit on his bed where he used to live and got the chills. Everyone in our group was moved to tears on this visit. If you ever go to Greece, add this to your trip. St. Nectarios helps so many and has granted so many miracles. I like to say believe in the unbelievable because nothing is too far from possible when you believe in St. Nectarios. 🙏❤️🇬🇷

Wonder over Worry

“CHOOSE WONDER OVER WORRY’ by hypnotherapist Ida Kendall. 

Worrying is an automatic mental habit that keeps you stuck and increases stress. 

Worrying places preoccupation on what isn’t working.\

We never find solutions when worried. Relaxation after worrying is when solutions come. 

Wondering is a mental expansion and an invitation to creative problem-solving.

Wondering is you taking control and actively deciding not to let anxiety and fear control you.

Wondering is prioritizing curiosity, awe, and fascination over anxiety or dread,  allowing for the possibility that curiosity can lead to ideas and solutions. 

Wondering is a perspective that allows you to benefit from what your life experiences are asking of you and the possibility there’s something more. 

Every time you wonder about something, instead of worrying about it, you are embracing the present moment and cultivating resilience.

My Brain, My Healer

The brain possesses extraordinary neuroplasticity to reorganize and form new connections, adapt to new experiences, acquire new skills, and recover from various injuries or traumas.

Does anyone else feel like you get let down after each Jan 1st? We get all excited, believing this is THE year. We plan, we plot, and then life hits us. By the end of ‘22 I was just starting to feel good again after my Mom’s passing. I was working out and getting stronger with a baby on the way, then boom. In a moment life becomes so fragile. I love the Tony Robbin’s quote, “life is happening for you not to you” well, I couldn’t quite figure out how to apply it this time. Thankfully, God and St. Nectarios had other plans for me. With their help and everyone else’s from my family to friends, to fans even, here I am Dec 31 getting ready for the new year. I was hesitant about getting excited for 2024 based on my hopes being crushed. I don’t want to feel like a fool- a side of me feels it’s better to be neutral. BUT while I do believe neutral is safe, it’s not exciting, nor is it the life I want. So I’m shifting that and asking ‘why can’t 2024 be amazing?’ Much of it comes down to perception and what we choose it to be, despite the downs. The roller coaster goes up and down and that’s why we love it. We survive the down for the pleasure of up. The birth of my daughter months after major surgery was only sweeter.
